

=Bio=

Director of Planning and  Community Development for the [http://www.montpelier-vt.org/ City of Montpelier], Founder and former Executive Director of Global Community Initiatives , former Deputy Secretary of the Vermont Agency of  Natural Resources, former Community Action Director for the Institute for  Sustainable Communities.  Co-Founder of Vermonters for a New Economy, a grassroots campaign fo change Vermont's economy.  Founder and Developer of the Headwaters Garden and Learning Center, an ecovillage in Cabot, Vermont.  Co-founder of the Onion River Exchange, a regional Time Bank and REACH, a Care Bank.

=Publications=

Author of The Key to Sustainable Cities:  Meeting Human Needs, Transforming Community Systems, (with Bernard Lietaer) Creating Wealth:  Growing Local Economies with Local Currencies, Community Currency, EarthCAT: Taking Action for Sustainability, and LASER: Local Action for Sustainable Economic Renewal.

